y%20asking%20me%20to%20bring%20them%20in.%20But%20the%20school%20in%20Berlin%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20will%20not%20call%20you.%20That%20is%20your%20child's%20responsibility.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsurprising-things-moving-to-germany-from-us-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI%20was%20a%20little%20shocked%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20has%20taught%20both%20me%20and%20my%20kids%20that%20they're%20capable%20of%20more%20than%20we%20thought%20they%20were.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2242064682-2b94-40ea-9f20-e8834d3122d2%5C%22%3EI'm%20proud%20of%20my%20children%20for%20becoming%20more%20independent%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20I%20do%20crave%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20control.%20But%20I'm%20so%20grateful%20for%20every%20child%20that%20my%20kids%20have%20become%20friends%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChildren%20are%20the%20best%20teachers%20to%20other%20children.%20My%20kids%20watch%20their%20friends%20and%20are%20learning%20to%20live%20a%20life%20where%20they%20are%20much%20more%20accountable%20for%20their%20choices%20and%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20my%20son%20left%20his%20lunch%20at%20home.%20Before%2C%20I%20would've%20panicked%20if%20I%20saw%20his%20lunchbox%20was%20still%20on%20the%20counter%2C%20thinking%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%20my%20goodness%2C%20he%20didn't%20eat%20today.%26quot%3B%20But%20later%20that%20day%2C%20he%20told%20me%20that%20after%20noticing%20he'd%20forgotten%20his%20lunch%2C%20a%20friend%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BLet's%20just%20go%20buy%20you%20a%20pretzel%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20they%20figured%20out%20a%20solution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20weird%20for%20me.%20I%20still%20want%20my%20kids%20to%20need%20me%20in%20some%20ways%2C%20but%20our%20relationship%20has%20changed%20to%20the%20point%20where%20there's%20less%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparental-stress-is-a-public-health-crisis-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emental%