20victor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ae98d881-be9b-4e56-8ea5-6c026bf7feb3%5C%22%3EAhead%20of%20the%20pack%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20before%20Biden%20ended%20his%20reelection%20bid%2C%20swing-state%20Democrats%20running%20in%20the%20most%20competitive%20Senate%20races%20were%20generally%20leading%20in%20the%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Biden%20struggled%20in%20his%20matchup%20against%20Trump%2C%20many%20voters%20earlier%20this%20year%20had%20already%20began%20to%20differentiate%20between%20the%20presidential%20race%20and%20down-ballot%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20eagerly%20thrown%20his%20support%20behind%20GOP%20Senate%20candidates%20like%20Kari%20Lake%20of%20Arizona%2C%20Mike%20Rogers%20of%20Michigan%2C%20Bernie%20Moreno%20of%20Ohio%2C%20and%20David%20McCormick%20of%20Pennsylvania.%20And%20he's%20implored%20his%20supporters%20to%20vote%20for%20these%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Democrats%20in%20these%20races%20have%20largely%20defied%20the%20conventional%20political%20norms%20of%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20latest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F09%2F28%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Ftrump-voters-ticket-splitting.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20Times%2FSiena%20College%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20five%20competitive%20Senate%20races%2C%20an%20average%20of%207%25%20of%20likely%20voters%20indicated%20they%20would%20back%20Trump%20while%20also%20pulling%20the%20lever%20for%20a%20Democratic%20Senate%20candidate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20polled%20states%20included%20Arizona%2C%20Michigan%2C%20Ohio%2C%20Pennsylvania%2C%20and%20Wisconsin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20five%20states%2C%20Ohio%20is%20most%20likely%20to%20vote%20for%20Trump%2C%20as%20he%20easily%20won%20it%20in%20both%202016%20and%202020.%20And%20the%20most%20recent%20Times%2FSiena%20survey%20showed%20Trump%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2024%2F09%2F28%2Fus%2Felections%2Ftimes-siena-ohio-crosstabs.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20six-point%20advantage%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20Harris%20(50%25%20to%2044%25)%20in%20the%20Buckeye%20State%20among%20likely%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227881%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Elissa%20Slotkin.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66f9b4d57518aa57bc9f0f77%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225254%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDemocratic%20Rep.%20Elissa%20Slotkin%20has%20held%20leads%20in%20the%20most%20recent%20Senate%20polls%20in%20Michigan%2C%20a%20highly%20competitive%20state%20on%20the%20presidential%20level.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Harnik%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20that%20same%20poll%2C%20Democratic%20Sen.%20Sherrod%20Brown%20had%20a%20four-point%20edge%20over%20Moreno%20among%20likely%20voters%20(47%25%20to%2043%25).%20Brown%20also%20won%20over%2013%25%20of%20Republicans%20in%20the%20poll%2C%20a%20level%20of%20crossover%20support%20that%20helps%20him%20in%20the%20red-trending%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Times%2FSiena%20poll%20also%20showed%20Democratic%20Rep.%20Ruben%20Gallego%20leading%20Lake%20by%20six%20points%20(49%25%20to%2043%25)%20in%20Arizona.%20In%20Michigan%2C%20Democratic%20Rep.%20Elissa%20Slotkin%20led%20Rogers%20by%20five%20points%20(47%25%20to%2042%25).%20And%20in%20Pennsylvania%20and%20Wisconsin%2C%20Sens.%20Bob%20Casey%20Jr.%20and%20Tammy%20Baldwin%20led%20their%20GOP%20opponents%20by%20nine%20and%20seven%20points%20among%20likely%20voters%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2208e6ae98-e83f-46e6-9f04-8e6c2f5a6fd3%5C%22%3EWhy%20does%20this%20matter%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EShould%20Democrats%20run%20the%20table%20in%20the%20most%20competitive%20swing-state%20Senate%20races%2C%20it'll%20leave%20them%20on%20the%20cusp%20of%20holding%20on%20to%20a%20majority.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Democrats%2C%20winning%20both%20safe%20and%20swing-state%20races%20%E2%80%94%20along%20with%20Ohio%